UPDATE articles 
SET content = '{"en":"{\"en\":\"{\\\"en\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"en\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"en\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"en\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> In Turkey, “all-inclusive” usually covers the main buffet and standard snack spots, while à la carte restaurants are often a special add-on experience with rules: you may need a reservation, there may be a limited number of included visits (or a small surcharge), and popular time slots can fill quickly. The smartest approach is simple: treat à la carte as a planned highlight, not something you “figure out later”.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>First: what “à la carte” means in a Turkey resort context</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>In an all-inclusive resort, you’ll usually see two dining styles:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li><strong>Main restaurant (buffet):</strong> the default option, open daily, usually included</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li><strong>À la carte / specialty restaurants:</strong> themed dining experiences (often smaller, quieter, more “date night” feeling)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Buffet is your reliable daily engine. À la carte is your “special evening”.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>What UK travellers often misunderstand (so you won’t)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Misunderstanding #1: “All-inclusive means every restaurant is included.”</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Not always. Many resorts include the buffet and standard snack venues, while à la carte can be:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>included but limited (e.g., “one visit per stay”)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>included only for longer stays</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>included on specific nights</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>available with a surcharge</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Never assume à la carte is unlimited. Always check the exact rule for your booking.</p>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Misunderstanding #2: “We’ll just walk in.”</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Often you can’t. Reservations are common, especially at peak times.</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/luxury-dining-couple-sunset-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"A La Carte Restaurants in Turkey All-Inclusive: How It Works (UK-Friendly No-Surprises Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Türkiye''de A La Carte Restoranlar Nasıl Çalışır? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 2\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>UK-friendly tip:</strong> If you care about à la carte, do your reservation plan on day 1. It’s the easiest win of the trip.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>The most common à la carte models in Turkey all-inclusive (how it “usually” works)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Resorts vary, but these are the typical patterns you’ll run into:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li><strong>Model A: Included, but limited</strong><br>You get a set number of à la carte visits per stay. Often requires a reservation. Prime slots can fill.</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li><strong>Model B: Included for longer stays</strong><br>Short stays may not include it. Longer stays may include one or more visits.</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li><strong>Model C: Small surcharge per person</strong><br>Buffet is included daily. À la carte is treated like a premium upgrade. Reservation still required.</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li><strong>Model D: Included, but with restrictions</strong><br>Specific restaurants included, others paid. Specific days or times. Certain menu items may be extra.</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Ask “How many visits are included for our stay, and which restaurants count?” That’s the clarity question.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Reservations: the real game (and how to win it)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>If you want a smooth à la carte experience, treat reservations like theatre tickets: the best slots go first.</p>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>What to do on Day 1</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Find out how reservations work (desk, app, QR code, guest services, etc.)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Ask what time reservations open each day</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Book your preferred night early (especially for weekends and peak season)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>UK-friendly tip:</strong> Book one “special dinner” early in the trip — not on the last night. If anything changes, you still have time to adjust.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>When to book</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li><strong>Peak season:</strong> book as soon as possible</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li><strong>Shoulder season:</strong> still book early if you care about a specific time</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> If a resort has limited seating, “later” becomes “no availability”.</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/gourmet-plate-fine-dining-turkey-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"A La Carte Restaurants in Turkey All-Inclusive: How It Works (UK-Friendly No-Surprises Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Türkiye''de A La Carte Restoranlar Nasıl Çalışır? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 3\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Dress code: what it typically means (without overthinking)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Many resorts have a “smart casual” vibe for à la carte, even if the buffet is relaxed.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Practical expectations (UK-friendly)</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>A little more polished than poolside</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Footwear and cover-ups matter more</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Beachwear is usually not the vibe</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Pack one “nice evening” outfit. You don’t need formal — just not beachwear.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Food experience: how à la carte differs from buffet (so you pick the right nights)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>À la carte is often a different experience:</p>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>quieter atmosphere</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>table service</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>slower pace</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>more “date night” feeling</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>But it’s not automatically “better” than buffet — it’s different.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Choose à la carte for atmosphere and pace, not because you assume buffet is inferior.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>UK-friendly tip:</strong> Many people enjoy buffet most nights, then do à la carte once or twice for variety and a special evening.</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/wine-tasting-vineyard-turkey-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"A La Carte Restaurants in Turkey All-Inclusive: How It Works (UK-Friendly No-Surprises Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Türkiye''de A La Carte Restoranlar Nasıl Çalışır? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 4\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Kids and à la carte: what families should check</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Families can absolutely enjoy à la carte — but the rules can matter.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Check these points</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Are children welcome at all à la carte venues?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Are there kid-friendly menu options?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Does the restaurant allow earlier seating times?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Is the pace suitable for your child’s routine?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> If you have toddlers, early seating matters more than “themed cuisine”.</p>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Related: <a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/guide/all-inclusive-family-checklist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">All-Inclusive for Families: The Non-Negotiables</a>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>“Included” vs “extra”: the simple way to avoid surprises</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Instead of trying to guess, use this checklist approach:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Ask these five questions</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>How many à la carte visits are included in our booking?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Which restaurants count as “included”?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Do we need a reservation — and how do we book?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Are there any surcharges per person or for premium items?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Are drinks included the same way as in the buffet restaurant?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> If you have answers to these five, you will not be surprised.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Related: <a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/guide/hidden-costs-turkey-resorts\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">Hidden Costs in Turkey Resorts (What UK Travellers Get Surprised By)</a>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Best practice: how to get the best à la carte experience</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>1) Pick the right night</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Not your arrival night (you’ll be tired)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Not your last night (risk of “no slots” or schedule stress)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Choose a night you can keep calm and enjoy</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>2) Choose the right time</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Earlier seating = easier for families</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Later seating = better for couples who like slow evenings</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>3) Treat it like a highlight, not a default</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>If you go in expecting it to be “the main way you’ll eat”, you might be disappointed if bookings are limited.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Plan 1–2 à la carte nights, and let buffet cover the rest.</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/chef-preparing-meal-open-kitchen-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"A La Carte Restaurants in Turkey All-Inclusive: How It Works (UK-Friendly No-Surprises Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Türkiye''de A La Carte Restoranlar Nasıl Çalışır? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 5\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>4) Keep your expectations realistic</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>À la carte is a holiday experience, not a Michelin competition. You’re paying for atmosphere, service, and variety.</p>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Copy-paste questions (send these in a message or ask at check-in)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>“How many à la carte visits are included in our stay?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>“Which restaurants are included vs paid?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>“How do reservations work — and what time do bookings open?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>“Are drinks included in à la carte the same as the main restaurant?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>“Is there a dress code?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>“Are children welcome, and is there an early seating option?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>“If there’s a surcharge, is it per person or per table?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>“What’s the best night to book if we want a calm atmosphere?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Quick checklist: à la carte in Turkey all-inclusive (save this)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Confirm “included vs extra” rules ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Book your preferred night on Day 1 ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Pack one smart-casual outfit ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>Decide if you want 1–2 highlight dinners or more ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    <li>If travelling with kids: check early seating + menu ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Reservation + clarity = zero stress.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>FAQ: À la carte restaurants in Turkey all-inclusive</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Are à la carte restaurants free in Turkey all-inclusive?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Sometimes, but often with limits. Many resorts include the main buffet daily and offer à la carte as a limited included visit or with a small surcharge. Always check your booking details.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Do I need to reserve à la carte restaurants?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Usually yes, especially in peak season and for popular time slots. The safest approach is to ask how reservations work on Day 1 and book early.</p>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>How many times can we use à la carte?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>It depends on the resort and your booking. Some include one visit per stay, some include more for longer stays, and some charge per visit.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Is the dress code strict?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Most places are “smart casual” rather than formal. The goal is simply to avoid beachwear. Pack one nice evening outfit and you’re covered.</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/couple-toasting-sunset-view-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"A La Carte Restaurants in Turkey All-Inclusive: How It Works (UK-Friendly No-Surprises Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Türkiye''de A La Carte Restoranlar Nasıl Çalışır? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 6\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Are drinks included at à la carte?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>It depends. Some resorts include the same drinks as the main restaurant, while others have different rules for premium items. Ask specifically to avoid surprises.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Can families use à la carte restaurants?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Often yes, but check child policy, menu options, and seating times. For toddlers, an early seating option is usually the most important detail.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tr\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<p>Bu içerik sadece İngilizce dilinde yayındadır.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tr\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<p>Content available in English only.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}</p>\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"tr\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"<p>Content available in English only.</p>\\\\\\\"}</p>\\\",\\\"tr\\\":\\\"<p>Content available in English only.</p>\\\"}</p>\",\"tr\":\"<p>Content available in English only.</p>\"}</p>","tr":"<p>Content available in English only.</p>"}'::jsonb, 
    cover_image_url = '/images/articles/alacarte_romantic_dinner_1770577127682.png',
    updated_at = NOW()
