UPDATE articles 
SET content = '{"en":"{\"en\":\"{\\\"en\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"en\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"en\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"en\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> For many UK travellers, a package holiday is the easiest way to get Turkey right: one booking, clear inclusions, and often a smoother transfer set-up. Booking separately can be great value and gives more flexibility, especially if you want a mixed itinerary or you’re confident organising logistics. The best choice isn’t “which is cheaper” — it’s which option gives you the best total cost (money + time + mental effort) for your travel style.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>The UK decision in one minute (pick your profile)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Choose the line that sounds most like you:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“We want easy. We don’t want to think.” → <strong>Package</strong></li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“We want flexibility and we’re happy to plan.” → <strong>Separate</strong></li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“We’re travelling with kids and want minimal friction.” → <strong>Package (usually)</strong></li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“We want to change bases / do day trips / move around.” → <strong>Separate (often)</strong></li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“We’re bargain-hunting and comparing lots of options.” → <strong>Either, but use the framework</strong></li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“We want protection and simple support if plans change.” → <strong>Package (usually)</strong></li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> If stress costs you more than money, package is often the best “value”.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>First: stop comparing headline price (use “Total Cost”)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>A package might look more expensive — until you count what’s included. Booking separately might look cheaper — until you add hidden extras.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Total Cost = Money + Time + Mental Load</strong>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li><strong>Money:</strong> flights, accommodation, transfers, add-ons, luggage, meals (if not all-inclusive)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> searching, comparing, booking, managing changes</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li><strong>Mental load:</strong> arrival-day decisions, coordination, problem-solving</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>UK-friendly tip:</strong> If your holiday is short, the mental load of DIY planning can be a bigger cost than you realise.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>What packages usually do well in Turkey (for UK travellers)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Package holidays often work particularly well for Turkey because they can bundle the parts that cause friction:</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/laptop-flight-booking-screen-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"Package Holiday vs Booking Separately for Turkey: UK Cost Comparison Framework (No-Guesswork Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Paket Tur mu Ayrı Rezervasyon mu? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 2\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>1) One booking, one set of details</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>fewer confirmations to manage</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>easier to communicate changes (in many cases)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>2) Transfers are often sorted (or at least offered clearly)</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Transfers are where DIY trips can get messy if you haven’t planned.</p>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Related: <a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/guide/turkey-resort-transfers-guide\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">Resort Transfers in Turkey: Reliable Options and What to Avoid</a>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>3) Clear “holiday rhythm”</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>If you’re booking all-inclusive, packages can make the whole trip feel like one smooth product.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>4) Strong fit for families and first-timers</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Families often benefit from:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>fewer moving parts</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>simpler arrival day</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>predictable structure</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Family guide: <a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/guide/all-inclusive-family-checklist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">All-Inclusive for Families: The Non-Negotiables</a>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Packages are best when you want the trip to feel like a single, tidy plan.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>What booking separately does better (when you know what you want)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Booking separately can be brilliant — but it’s not automatically better.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>1) Flexibility</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>choose flight times that suit you</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>mix different accommodation styles (still no hotel names here, but you get the idea)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>change bases (city + coast trips)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Itinerary frameworks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/guide/turkey-itinerary-7-days-first-time\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">Turkey Itinerary (7 Days): The Best First-Time Plan</a>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>2) Potential value for confident planners</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>If you’re good at planning, you can:</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/travel-agency-brochures-desk-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"Package Holiday vs Booking Separately for Turkey: UK Cost Comparison Framework (No-Guesswork Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Paket Tur mu Ayrı Rezervasyon mu? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 3\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>build your own “best fit” trip</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>avoid paying for bundled extras you won’t use</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>3) Better for “mixed holidays”</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>If you want 2–3 different experiences in one trip (city + coast, exploring-heavy), DIY planning often fits.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Book separately if you want a trip with more than one “mode”.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>The UK cost comparison framework (use this to decide)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Don’t ask “Which is cheaper?” Ask these five questions:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Question 1: How many moving parts can you handle?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>If you want fewer decisions → package</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>If you enjoy planning and can manage details → separate</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> Your tolerance for admin is part of the budget.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Question 2: Is your arrival day likely to be stressful?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Consider:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>landing late</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>travelling with kids</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>multiple suitcases</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>short trip length</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>If yes, package transfers (or pre-planned private transfer) becomes more valuable.</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/airport-transfer-bus-shuttle-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"Package Holiday vs Booking Separately for Turkey: UK Cost Comparison Framework (No-Guesswork Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Paket Tur mu Ayrı Rezervasyon mu? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 4\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Question 3: Do you need flexibility?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>If you want specific flight times, a split stay, or changes → separate</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>If you want one smooth “resort week” → package</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Question 4: Do you care about “vibe matching”?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>If you’re very sensitive to:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>quiet vs lively</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>adults-only vibe vs family energy</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>sleep quality</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Then booking separately can help you choose more precisely — but only if you’re willing to research properly.</p>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Adults-only guide: <a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/guide/adults-only-all-inclusive-turkey-guide\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">Adults-Only All-Inclusive: How to Choose</a>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Question 5: What does “value” mean for you?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>families: value = easy routines</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>couples: value = calm + good evenings</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>explorers: value = flexibility</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>resort-lovers: value = on-site variety</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Value guide: <a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/guide/best-all-inclusive-value-uk-turkey\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">How to Get the Best All-Inclusive Value from the UK</a>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>What to compare line-by-line (so it’s a fair fight)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Whether you’re comparing package vs DIY, compare these items:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>A) Flights</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>flight times and convenience</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>luggage allowances (what you actually need)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>total travel time and connections</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>B) Transfers</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>included vs extra</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>private vs shared</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>arrival-time suitability (late arrivals need simplicity)</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>C) Food plan</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>all-inclusive vs half-board vs room-only</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>your daily rhythm: will you eat out often?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>D) Room type / layout</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>This matters more than most people think, especially for families.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Room logic: <a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/guide/best-all-inclusive-value-uk-turkey\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">How to Get the Best All-Inclusive Value (Room Types)</a>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>E) Change flexibility</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>can you change names, dates, or flight times?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>what happens if plans change?</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> If you can’t compare these five areas, you’re not comparing total cost.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Common UK mistakes (and how to avoid them)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Mistake 1: Choosing DIY for “savings” then paying in stress</strong>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Fix: if you want DIY, plan transfers and arrival day properly.</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/villa-rental-pool-view-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"Package Holiday vs Booking Separately for Turkey: UK Cost Comparison Framework (No-Guesswork Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Paket Tur mu Ayrı Rezervasyon mu? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 5\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Mistake 2: Choosing a package but not reading the inclusions</strong>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Fix: confirm transfers, baggage, and what “all-inclusive” includes for your booking.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Mistake 3: Comparing a premium package to a barebones DIY plan</strong>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Fix: compare like-for-like: same board basis, same transfer type, same luggage.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Mistake 4: Forgetting the “energy cost”</strong>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Fix: if you’re doing a short trip, simplicity is worth more.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>When package is usually the smarter choice (UK scenarios)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You’re travelling with young kids</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You’re a first-time Turkey visitor</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You’re landing late or you want a smooth arrival</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You want a classic all-inclusive week</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You don’t want to coordinate multiple bookings</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You want simple support if things change</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> If the goal is “easy holiday”, package often wins.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>When booking separately is usually better (UK scenarios)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You want a city + coast split</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You care about specific flight times</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You like building your own itinerary</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You want short stays in multiple places</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You’re comfortable organising transfers and logistics</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>You want maximum control</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> If the goal is “custom holiday”, separate often wins.</p>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Copy-paste questions (use these before you decide)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Paste these into your notes or ask a travel agent:</p>\n<figure class=\"my-8\">\n<img src=\"/images/articles/calculator-travel-budget-planning-1767986408887.jpg\" alt=\"{\"en\":\"Package Holiday vs Booking Separately for Turkey: UK Cost Comparison Framework (No-Guesswork Guide)\",\"tr\":\"Paket Tur mu Ayrı Rezervasyon mu? (TR Pasif)\"} - Image 6\" class=\"w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg\" loading=\"lazy\" onError=\"this.onerror=null;this.src=''/images/articles/turkey_holiday_generic_1767986408887.jpg'';\" />\n</figure>\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“What exactly is included in the package price (transfers, luggage, board basis)?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“If we book separately, what will transfers cost and how do we arrange them?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“How much flexibility do we have if flight times change?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“Are we comparing the same room type and board basis?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“Are there any resort extras we’re likely to pay for?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>“Which option gives us the easiest arrival day?”</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>Quick checklist: package vs separate (UK)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Tick the statements that are true for you:</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Package likely suits you if:</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We want minimal decisions ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We want transfers sorted ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We’re travelling with kids ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We want a classic all-inclusive week ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We value simplicity over customisation ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Booking separately likely suits you if:</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We want flexibility and control ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We want a split stay (city + coast) ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We’re confident planning transfers ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We want specific flight times ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<li>We enjoy itinerary-building ✅</li>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n</ul>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p><strong>Simple rule:</strong> If one side has clearly more ticks, that’s your answer.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h2>FAQ: Package holiday vs booking separately for Turkey (UK)</h2>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Are package holidays to Turkey cheaper from the UK?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Sometimes, but not always. The better question is total cost: packages often include transfers and simplify planning. Booking separately can be cheaper if you plan well and you don’t need bundled extras.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Is booking separately risky?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Not necessarily. It’s just more admin. If you book flights, accommodation, and transfers thoughtfully, DIY trips can be smooth — especially for mixed itineraries.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Which is better for families?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Packages are often easier for families because they reduce moving parts and usually make arrival day simpler. Families also benefit from predictable routines and fewer logistics decisions.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>Which is better for couples?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Couples can enjoy either. Packages can feel effortless for a calm reset. Booking separately can be great if you want a more customised itinerary or specific flight times.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>What’s the best way to compare fairly?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Compare like-for-like: same board basis, same luggage needs, same transfer type, same room type. Then add the “time + mental load” factor.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<h3>What if we want to do a city + coast trip?</h3>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n<p>Booking separately is often the best fit because you can control timing and split your trip across two bases without trying to fit a package template.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tr\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<p>Bu içerik sadece İngilizce dilinde yayındadır.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tr\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<p>Content available in English only.</p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}</p>\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"tr\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"<p>Content available in English only.</p>\\\\\\\"}</p>\\\",\\\"tr\\\":\\\"<p>Content available in English only.</p>\\\"}</p>\",\"tr\":\"<p>Content available in English only.</p>\"}</p>","tr":"<p>Content available in English only.</p>"}'::jsonb, 
